course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees.

Remove @Italian Pork Sausage{9%ounce} from casing; discard casing.

> TIP: Use kitchen shears or a sharp knife to cut a slit in the casing lengthwise; it's a quick way to de-case the sausage!

Heat @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add sausage and half the @Italian Seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

While sausage cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @Cornstarch{2%tablespoon} and @Water{1/2%cup} until combined.

Add @Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce} to #pot{} with sausage. Cook, stirring occasionally, until combined, ~{30%seconds}.

Increase heat to high. Stir in @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1}, cornstarch mixture, and @Water{1 1/2%cups}(hot); bring to a boil. Cook until thickened, ~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: If soup seems too thick, stir in another 1/4 cup of water.

Remove pot from heat; stir in @Peas{4%ounce}. Taste and season generously with @Salt{3/4%tsp} and @Pepper{}.

While soup cooks, halve @Demi-Baguette{1} lengthwise. Place, cut sides up, on a #baking sheet{}. Sprinkle with @Italian Cheese Blend{1/4%cup}.

Bake on top rack until cheese melts, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Divide soup between #bowls{}; top with remaining @Italian Cheese Blend{1/4%cup}. Serve with cheesy bread on the side.